quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  41,1,"Ha Mīm."
  41,2,"A bestowal from on high by the All-Merciful, the Bestower of mercy—"
  41,3,"a Scripture whose signs{1}were detailed as an Arabic Recital{2}for people who know.",1:[The Arabic word used is <i>ayat</i> (singular <i>ayah</i>). <i>Ayah</i> means ‘sign’ or ‘proof’. It is also used to denote the unit of text in the Qur’an, like ‘verse’ in poetry or ‘sentence’ in prose. Each such unit is considered a ‘sign’ from God.],2:[The Arabic word used is <i>Qur’an</i> which literally means ‘recital’ or ‘recitation’.]
  41,4,"A herald of glad tidings and a warner, but most of them disregard<i>(it), </i>so they do not hear."
  41,5,"And they said, “Our hearts are screened from what you<sup>sg </sup>call us to, and in our ears is deafness, and between us and you is a barrier. So do what you want, and so will we.”"
  41,6,"Say<sup>sg </sup>, “I am only a human being like you<sup>pl </sup>. To me it is revealed that your god is One God. So be upright towards Him and seek forgiveness from Him.” And woe to the polytheists—"
  41,7,"those who do not bring about the purifying act{1}, and regarding the Hereafter they are deniers.",1:[The Arabic word here, <i>zak</i><i>āt</i>, is the same word used for purifying charity, and which literally means purification and growth.]
  41,8,"Indeed, those who have attained faith and have done righteous deeds—for them is an unfailing reward."
  41,9,"Say, “Can it be that you<sup>pl </sup>really deny the One Who created the earth in two<i>(heavenly) </i>days and attribute rivals to Him? That is the Lord of all realms.”"
  41,10,"And He made therein firm mountains on top of it, and He blessed it and determined its sustenance in four days, equal,{1}for those who ask.",1:[Qira’at: Abu Ja’far read it as: “…in four days; (they are) equal for those who ask.” Ya’qub read it as: “…in four equal days for those who ask.”]
